                                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.—<name type="person">Private John T. Cole</name>, <name type="organization">Co. A, 10th Vermont Volunteers</name>, aged 24 years, was wounded at
                                                                <name type="BATTLE" key="254">Petersburg</name>, <date type="injury" when="1865-04-02">April 2d, 1865</date>, by a conoidal ball, which entered just above the left zygoma, passed
                                                  through the orbit, and emerged through the outer
                                                  and upper portion of the right orbital structure,
                                                  destroying both eyes. He was, on <date type="admit" when="1865-04-03">the following
                                                  day</date>, admitted to the <name type="hospital">depot field hospital at City
                                                                  Point</name>; on <date type="transfer" when="1865-04-07">April 7th</date>, sent to the<name type="hospital" key="176">Lincoln Hospital</name>, Washington, and, on <date type="transfer" when="1865-05-26">May 26th</date>, transferred to the
                                                                <name type="hospital">Sloan Hospital, Montpelier, Vermont</name>. At this time
                                                  the wound of entrance had healed and the general
                                                  health of the patient was good, but lying on the
                                                  left side would cause headache; the sense of smell
                                                  was entirely destroyed. Cold water dressings were
                                                  applied; during the treatment, small pieces of
                                                  bone were taken from the wound of entrance.
                                                  Otherwise the case progressed well, and, on <date type="servicedischarge" when="1865-06-12">June
                                                  12th, 1865</date>, Cole was discharged from service and
                                                  pensioned at $25 per month</p>
                                                
